 Blinx, who just last month released a collaboration EP ‘AFRO FROM A TRAP HOUSE’ with creative partner Doe Billz, has informed us that his debut studio album project is good to go. He made the revelation during a brief chat with our correspondent. Obinna Okolie better known as ‘Blinx’ is a South Africa based Nigerian trap rapper, songwriter and producer. Obi also hinted that he will be dropping 3 singles to herald the forthcoming album.“BAD featuring Notory & Doe Billz and produced by Sierprincey will be the first single from the album followed by NO BODY & YEAH! YEAH! YEAH!,” He stated. Blinx also revealed that the video for BAD has already been shot on location in Capetown, and was directed by Juzzy. “The album is still untitled and consists of 20 tracks, though I already have September as the official release month. BAD will be the first serving from the project and will give my fans a taste of what to expect,” Blinx said. According to Blinx, this will be his first ever studio project, and will include features from several South African and Nigerian artists as well. Blinx already has 2 EPs to his credit, a solo effort, “PAIN, SUFFERING & SACRIFICE” (PSS) released in 2021 and a joint project ‘AFRO FROM A TRAP HOUSE’ (AFATH) in collaborative partnership with Doe Billz.